Recycle centres

Recycle centres convert waste into ore. Labor, electric power (low-voltage) and money are used to collect the waste and convert it into raw ore. They can be used to empty previously filled tips.

It is possible to run a sustainable economy, (i.e. no more ore extracted, etc) with less than 100% efficient recycle centres if you have some mills to make up for the losses.

